The paper deals with the generation of 3D maps of urban facades using computer vision techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of 3D point clouds and area-based information suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper describes a practical approach for completing and recovering facade geometry and textures, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms and data complementarity, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
